translated: Lindeborg, Angelo Waldemar, curate, Åtvidaberg, b. 29/7/90 in Stockholm, the son of the engraver Johan Ludvig L. and Ida Kobel. Married in 1925 to Jane Breitholtz. Children: Hans, born in 1926, office clerk, Jane, born in 1929, Claes, born in 1937. Ordained in the Linköping Diocese in 1920. Served as a vicar in Regna and Hjorted, vicar and acting curate in Åtvid from 1925, appointed curate there in 1927, and deputy vicar since 1943. Served as a substitute in the church council, chairman of the pension committee and election committee, children's guardian, substitute in the municipal council and school board, part-time teacher in the municipality, and secretary in the Åtvids hemibygds-fören (local heritage association). Writings: Confirmation and sermon speeches for confirmation students. A member of the National Gymnastics Federation, Swedish Cycling Association stipulatonsm., and has earned recognition in swimming.
